{ id: 'algo-03-04-order-growth', parentId: 'folder-algo-analysis', name: '04. Order-of-Growth Classifications', type: NodeType.FILE, content: `# Order of Growth

## Common Classifications
| Growth | Name | Description | Example |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| $1$ | Constant | No loops | Add two numbers |
| $\\log N$ | Logarithmic | Divide in half | Binary Search |
| $N$ | Linear | Loop | Find max |
| $N \\log N$ | Linearithmic | Divide & Conquer | Mergesort |
| $N^2$ | Quadratic | Double loop | Bubble Sort |
| $N^3$ | Cubic | Triple loop | 3-Sum |
| $2^N$ | Exponential | Combinatorial | subsets |

## Binary Search Analysis
**Theorem**: Binary search uses at most $1 + \lg N$ compares.
**Cost**: Logarithmic.

### Interactive Analysis: Linear vs Binary
Compare the number of steps required to find a target.

\`\`\`search
